30static bool c_tree_printer (pretty_printer *, text_info *, const char *,
31 int, bool, bool, bool);
32
33bool
34c_missing_noreturn_ok_p (tree decl)
35{
36 /* A missing noreturn is not ok for freestanding implementations and
37 ok for the `main' function in hosted implementations. */
38 return flag_hosted && MAIN_NAME_P (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (decl));
39}

41/* Called from check_global_declaration. */
42
43bool
44c_warn_unused_global_decl (const_tree decl)
45{
46 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL && DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl))
47 return false;
48 if (DECL_IN_SYSTEM_HEADER (decl))
49 return false;
50
51 return true;
52}

56c_objc_common_init (void)

58 c_init_decl_processing ();
59
60 return c_common_init ();

63/* Called during diagnostic message formatting process to print a
64 source-level entity onto BUFFER. The meaning of the format specifiers
65 is as follows:
66 %D: a general decl,
67 %E: an identifier or expression,
68 %F: a function declaration,
69 %T: a type.
70 %V: a list of type qualifiers from a tree.
71 %v: an explicit list of type qualifiers
72 %#v: an explicit list of type qualifiers of a function type.
73
74 Please notice when called, the `%' part was already skipped by the
75 diagnostic machinery. */
76static bool
77c_tree_printer (pretty_printer *pp, text_info *text, const char *spec,
78 int precision, bool wide, bool set_locus, bool hash)
79{
80 tree t = NULL_TREE;
81 tree name;
82 // FIXME: the next cast should be a dynamic_cast, when it is permitted.
83 c_pretty_printer *cpp = (c_pretty_printer *) pp;
84 pp->padding = pp_none;
85
86 if (precision != 0 || wide)
87 return false;
88
89 if (*spec == 'K')
90 {
91 percent_K_format (text);
92 return true;
93 }
94
95 if (*spec != 'v')
96 {
97 t = va_arg (*text->args_ptr, tree);
98 if (set_locus)
99 text->set_location (0, DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (t), true);
100 }
101
102 switch (*spec)
103 {
104 case 'D':
105 if (VAR_P (t) && DECL_HAS_DEBUG_EXPR_P (t))
106 {
107 t = DECL_DEBUG_EXPR (t);
108 if (!DECL_P (t))
109 {
110 cpp->expression (t);
111 return true;
112 }
113 }
114 /* FALLTHRU */
115
116 case 'F':
117 if (DECL_NAME (t))
118 {
119 pp_identifier (cpp, lang_hooks.decl_printable_name (t, 2));
120 return true;
121 }
122 break;
123
124 case 'T':
125 {
126 gcc_assert (TYPE_P (t));
127 struct obstack *ob = pp_buffer (cpp)->obstack;
128 char *p = (char *) obstack_base (ob);
129 /* Remember the end of the initial dump. */
130 int len = obstack_object_size (ob);
131
132 name = TYPE_NAME (t);
133 if (name && TREE_CODE (name) == TYPE_DECL && DECL_NAME (name))
134 pp_identifier (cpp, lang_hooks.decl_printable_name (name, 2));
135 else
136 cpp->type_id (t);
137
138 /* If we're printing a type that involves typedefs, also print the
139 stripped version. But sometimes the stripped version looks
140 exactly the same, so we don't want it after all. To avoid
141 printing it in that case, we play ugly obstack games. */
142 if (TYPE_CANONICAL (t) && t != TYPE_CANONICAL (t))
143 {
144 c_pretty_printer cpp2;
145 /* Print the stripped version into a temporary printer. */
146 cpp2.type_id (TYPE_CANONICAL (t));
147 struct obstack *ob2 = cpp2.buffer->obstack;
148 /* Get the stripped version from the temporary printer. */
149 const char *aka = (char *) obstack_base (ob2);
150 int aka_len = obstack_object_size (ob2);
151 int type1_len = obstack_object_size (ob) - len;
152
153 /* If they are identical, bail out. */
154 if (aka_len == type1_len && memcmp (p + len, aka, aka_len) == 0)
155 return true;
156
157 /* They're not, print the stripped version now. */
158 pp_c_whitespace (cpp);
159 pp_left_brace (cpp);
160 pp_c_ws_string (cpp, _("aka"));
161 pp_c_whitespace (cpp);
162 cpp->type_id (TYPE_CANONICAL (t));
163 pp_right_brace (cpp);
164 }
165 return true;
166 }
167
168 case 'E':
169 if (TREE_CODE (t) == IDENTIFIER_NODE)
170 pp_identifier (cpp, IDENTIFIER_POINTER (t));
171 else
172 cpp->expression (t);
173 return true;
174
175 case 'V':
176 pp_c_type_qualifier_list (cpp, t);
177 return true;
178
179 case 'v':
180 pp_c_cv_qualifiers (cpp, va_arg (*text->args_ptr, int), hash);
181 return true;
182
183 default:
184 return false;
185 }
186
187 pp_string (cpp, _("({anonymous})"));
188 return true;
189}

191/* In C and ObjC, all decls have "C" linkage. */
192bool
193has_c_linkage (const_tree decl ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
194{
195 return true;
196}
197
198void
199c_initialize_diagnostics (diagnostic_context *context)
200{
201 pretty_printer *base = context->printer;
202 c_pretty_printer *pp = XNEW (c_pretty_printer);
203 context->printer = new (pp) c_pretty_printer ();
204
205 /* It is safe to free this object because it was previously XNEW()'d. */
206 base->~pretty_printer ();
207 XDELETE (base);
208
209 c_common_diagnostics_set_defaults (context);
210 diagnostic_format_decoder (context) = &c_tree_printer;
211}
212
213int
214c_types_compatible_p (tree x, tree y)
215{
216 return comptypes (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (x), TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (y));
217}

219/* Determine if the type is a vla type for the backend. */
220
221bool
222c_vla_unspec_p (tree x, tree fn ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
223{
224 return c_vla_type_p (x);
225}
